MAMELODI Sundowns forward Percy Tau and coach Pitso Mosimane have been both crowned Absa Premiership player and coach of the month for April. It is for the second time this season that this same duo from The Brazillians clinch the PSL monthly accolades this season. In January Mosimane and Tau were announced as the winners for December‚ Tau becoming the first player in the history of the monthly awards to be unanimously selected by the judges. Sundowns won four out of five PSL matches in April. They beat Chippa United 2-0 at home‚ Baroka FC 2-1 away‚ Bidvest Wits 2-0 at home and Lamontville Golden Arrows 1-0 at home‚ in a four-match winning streak‚ then drew 2-2 away against Maritzburg United. Tau who is the favourite to walk with the Footballer of the Season award in the PSL Awards later this month‚ scored a goal against Chippa, against Baroka‚ and provided the assists for both goals  when Sundowns thumped Wits.